<p>Napa Valley's Mediterranean climate creates ideal conditions for premium wine production, with warm, dry summers and mild, wet winters. Average temperatures range from 60-80°F during the growing season, though this varies dramatically by location. The valley receives approximately 24-36 inches of annual rainfall, concentrated between November and April, allowing for dry harvest conditions. With over 300 days of sunshine annually, grapes achieve optimal phenolic ripeness while retaining crucial acidity through cool nighttime temperatures that can drop 40-50°F from daytime highs.</p>

