<p><strong>Cabernet Sauvignon from prestigious appellations</strong> like Oakville and Rutherford can age 15-25 years, with cult wines from Screaming Eagle or Harlan Estate developing for decades. The valley's structured tannins from mountain vineyards provide the backbone for extended aging.</p>

<p><strong>Chardonnay</strong> varies dramatically—unoaked versions peak within 3-5 years, while barrel-fermented examples from cooler sites like Carneros develop beautifully over 8-12 years, gaining honeyed complexity and mineral depth.</p>

